data.title: Furniture and Mattress Store Near Me
data.meta_description: Shop for furniture, mattresses, and home décor at your Southaven, MS Ashley Store. Visit our showroom today to furnish your home affordably.
data.text:
I went in to purchase a night stand and the saleswoman Allison ordered the incorrect color. I immediately notified her of the mistake and she told me her manager had to approve the return ticket. After a couple days of no communication I called and spoke with a male manager. He stated that he would start the ticket and Allison would get back with me. That never happened and after a day I called and spoke with a female manager and she told me she saw the notes but no ticket. She told me she put the ticket in and she’d give me a call when the warehouse approves it. ( have the text thread which also shows the conversation). After a few days still nothing and she stopped responding. I called the 1800 number and they stated I had to deal with the store I purchased from. Finally I went to the warehouse and the receptionist explained what I needed to do. I went to Winchester they gave me a return credit and I was able to go to the warehouse and pick up my nightstand. If the Southaven store would have used communication skills my problem would have been solved days ago. This store mission and vision cannot at all be able communication and quality service because I receive neither one and nothing was done about it. Thank you Winchester store for fixing a problem you did not create. I will never buy anything from the Southaven store again.

This experience has been extremely aggravating and frustrating for me. I did everything possible to ensure this purchase process was correct due to the fact I live in GA and could not return to the store physically. I was double billed and have had to call and report and explain this issue at least 5 times to different Ashley employees to no avail over the past 2 weeks. Today, I cannot have the furniture picked up because Ashley systems do not show I've paid for the furniture but my credit card has been charged again for this purchase as of 6/4/24. Ashley billing representative spoke with the credit card representative to obtain the transaction codes and dates. I hate that my family won't receive the new and seriously needed furniture today. I was told Ashley doesn't have a process to expedite this issue and I have to just wait until they find out what is wrong on their side. As the customer, I'm not priority for Ashley and I've encountered all the issues, made all the phone calls to try to resolve the issue with the exception of 2 call made to me from the warehouse and from the store yesterday. Terrible resolution process and no urgency for the customer. Dorothy Thomas

Went in to the Southaven store on Feb 26th. White guy passed us off to the the black guy. That's ok. I asked why. The answer was " He felt it was a better fit for us and the sale'" COOL!!! Placed the order. The sectional came first. It was ok but the chaise was on the wrong side. The table arrived 3 days later in a box. It was delivered to the wrong address even after we alerted them that the wrong address was on the paperwork and it as too big. Called the store. We were advised to call Guest Services. Have been trying for the last four days to get someone on the phone. The one day that we did get someone on the phone 1. we were told there was no refund on the table we didn't want and 2. we were put on hold to speak with a manager that never came on line after holding for 45 minutes. The guest service rep hug up. This is bad business and we will never buy anything from Ashley Furniture again while advising everyone we know to NEVER BUY anything. If there id no return, customers should be told. I guess then that would hurt sales. So why tell when it hurts Ashley's bottom line. We could have cancelled the order before delivery!!

My wife and I went to Ashley to look for a sectional. We found the one we loved and were excited to have it delivered that weekend. Unfortunately, once it delivered, we found that they brought two different colors and had to ask them to take it back. The delivery drivers left the pieces that were supposedly correct instead of taking everything back (later the store tried to hold us accountable for this when discussing returning all product). Our next thought was to obviously reach out to our sales rep that worked with us in store, who convinced us that he resolved the issue and that our next delivery would be correct, however, when it delivered, the color was still wrong. Meanwhile, we asked them about a tear in the fabric on one of the pieces that the drivers had left behind and were told we could not return it but they would ship us a fabric and a technician would come to install the fabric professionally. Not the best option in my opinion but that’s fine. Well Ashley sent pillow stuffing instead of fabric. Back to the sectional — upon talking with a manager, we get no clear answers. Looks like this is going to have to be a full return and looks like they’re going to make us fight for it.

HORRIBLE EXPERIENCE!!!! This has by far been the biggest headache I’ve had while ordering/receiving furniture. At the time of my visit to Ashley everything seemed great and my salesperson Shun seemed like he had me situated. But at the time of delivery, the sectional I ordered came in different colors (after being told by shun that only one color existed). I call him and the online customer care, and they both said it’s fixed. I scheduled my new delivery date and what do you know, it’s WRONG again. Two different colors are being delivered, so I tell them to take it back. I call the store and they’re basically saying they’re fixing it but they said that last time and it was a lie. At this point it’s been a week and a half that I’ve not had a couch and no one of the team is concerned and it has become a blame game on both parts of the corporation, the store front and the online customer care service. I AM DISGUSTED by the service and if they accepted returns I would have taken this back a long time ago but of course they just want money without providing quality service.

Disappointed! As long as there isn’t a problem after the sale, you should be ok. BUT if there is an issue, good luck! Purchased headboard, rails, footboard, nightstands, and chair on July 4. It was delivered Aug. 8. Two of the 6 pieces were not in boxes and 1 was in a busted open box. The delivery guy suggested to check for parts missing and damage. Bolts were missing as well as scratches and nicks on pieces not boxed. He took pics and said he would report it. My understanding was a replacement order would be started. That was on a Saturday. The following Monday (within the 3 days required notification of damage) I doubled checked with our salesperson. She said she could see a report was made by the delivery guy, and that I should receive a follow up call about redelivery. Again, understanding the pieces were being replaced. Then nothing. I called again on Sept. 7 left a message and was called back. She would check on it. I never received an answer about when the furniture would be delivered and that’s with going by the store on 9/16 and leaving additional messages Sept. 23 and 29. Finally, called the support line and learned no replacement was ever issued. A report was made and that was it. They would send me the replacement parts (bolts) and send a tech out. The parts came in the second week of October. I still have to schedule a tech to come out and fix the scratches. Honestly having to repair brand NEW furniture is ridiculous. To be fair, the pieces in a box were fine, and perhaps the sales people cannot do anything after the sell, but then tell me that and not keep saying, “I’ll check,” and never follow up. I understand they have to check for fraudulent claims, but good grief your delivery guy took pics when he delivered it!

Horrible experience. DO NOT use Beth. She screwed up our order so bad that we didn't even get everything we wanted. Her tablet died multiple times and one order got locked into it where we had to restart everything over again. She was flighty and all over the place and we feel as though we got 100% messed over after everything was said and done. The delivery team reeked of pot and brought in damaged furniture and was adamant to not take it back with them. The icing on the cake was a 'thank you' note that was mailed and handwritten by Beth, two weeks after we alerted Beth of the issues. She couldn't even manage to spell the name correctly on the envelope, let alone acknowledge the mess that was made in the store with the order or how we received damaged items. She thanked us and told us she's glad she could make our new move more enjoyable. What a joke. This has been a disaster. Still waiting for my replacement chair and a half. You'd think if you spent $6,500 in CASH, a place would take better care of you. EDIT They were supposed to send us a refund check regarding some of our damaged items. That was at least 6 months ago. No check in sight.

It wasn’t so much the store, the store and its associates were great and very helpful, however all we were trying to do was purchase 2 cushions as our dogs exploded 2 of them. My wife spent 2+ hours at the store on one day, the store associate kept getting put on hold or hung up on by the parts dept and finally was told that someone would be in touch. Almost 2 weeks later we finally get and email from the parts dept, told them what happened and then they said that they could not help and that I had to go to the store. We told them that they step was already done and they continued to refer us back to the store. So my wife went back today and it got handled but still took OVER and hour to get what we needed done. Bottom line, the stores and the parts department need to get together and do something different as that was stupid. There is no reason as to why All that cannot be accomplished in less than an hour.

Beyond the worst shopping experience. We bought a bedroom suite for kids on Sept 23, with "white glove" delivery scheduled for the 27. We were delivered half of a bunk bed, and the chest of drawers and dresser were both broken. Throughout our ordeal we have had their delivery team scheduled 5 different times. Every time something was broken or incomplete. We were told by the delivery team each time they would order something and reach out to us, but I'd have to call a week later to find out no one had put in an order. I asked for a refund numerous times which was denied. I finally spoke to the parts department to get replacement parts for the broken dresser and bunk bed. Something they admitted their associates should have done for me. Bunk bed parts arrived, and now they say they won't come put it together until dresser parts are in which will be in Dec. Everyone is bound by "store policy" and is incapable of finding realistic solutions. I have spent months of being lied to and having to jump through hoops to get furniture that isn't broken. They trap you with by their no refund policy even when they consistently deliver broken or incomplete orders. Save yourself the frustration and shop elsewhere!

Back in March I ordered a mattress, adjustable base, and a bed frame. I was told the bed frame was on back order until July or August but could get the mattress and adjustable base the following Tuesday. ALMOST A MONTH LATER they get delivered but the guys cut the power cord to the base. Contact Ashley and they said have to get ahold of Tempurpedic. Went to the store and was promised a new base. Week later got call from warehouse saying that isn’t going to happen I need to go through Tempurpedic. Contacted Tempurpedic and said they can’t do anything that Ashley had to replace it. Contacted Ashley again and told them Tempurpedic won’t replace it. The agent argued with me demanding I have to go through Tempurpedic. So I went back to the store and again promised me a new base. Two weeks after not hearing anything finally got a power cord to go with the base. Fast forward to now, get a notification that bed frame is ready for delivery. Schedule delivery and when they arrive, they are only there to pick up the useless loaner frame and no bed frame!! Contacted Ashley and they said waiting on the rails. They forgot to communicate that to me!! Now I’m ready to cancel the order for the bed frame. Read the other reviews. They’re not lying. Do not buy your furniture at Ashley!! Stay away!!!

If I could give a negative I sure would. I never got part of what I purchased and very disappointed with the management team and crew. I made my purchased on November 3 of 2021 and canceled it because after eight months I still had not received part of it. Yes I did change my order but at the same time I gave them plenty of time to fulfill it. Every time I spoke to the manager I got some kind of excuse or another. I got to the point I gave up and quit asking and because he refused to return my calls always promise to call me even give me a date or a or a time but never did.. It would be an injustice if I did not stop people to even open your doors in your store. I will never ever ever ever purchase anything from you, my children, my friends, or anybody in the freaking world. I hope this is the last time I write or waste a precious moment regarding Ashleys Furniture🤬🤬🤬🤬🤬🤬🤬🤬🤬🤬🤬

Edit: It’s been a couple of weeks and we still don’t have the correct table we ordered. The receptionist put me on hold to get a manager today and they left me on hold for 1 hour and 40 minutes, they only picked up the phone then because my husband drove over there. We paid for all of this furniture in February and it is now end of May and still no one can help us get it right. Be very careful if you buy from this store. The manager doesn’t return calls and threatened to call the police on us if we left the cocktail table there since it’s not the one we ordered. We will be following up with a letter from an attorney this week. We waited 6-7 weeks for our furniture to be delivered. 3 of the 5 items we ordered were not what we ordered. We tried to send them back that day and were told they couldn’t put them back on the truck and the store would contact us within 3 hours. We have called, messaged left messages with customer service and on voicemail and no one has returned our call. It’s been 6 days and still we haven’t hear from anyone but are told daily by customer service someone will call us back that day. This is the worst furniture buying experience we have ever had.

My wife and I purchased a Tempur Pedic mattress with the TEMPUR-Ergo 2.0 Split California King Adjustable Base in November of 2021 from the Ashley store in Southaven, MS. We also purchased a sectional couch at the same time. The sales person, Beth Hawkins, stated that we would NOT have to make ANY payments until we received all the merchandise for each order. The bed arrived in January and we started making payments in February as stated. The couch was scheduled to be delivered in February by was pushed out to April. We were fine with that until we received a bill March. I contacted the Ashley store in Southaven and they stated it was a billing error and they would correct it. Well, Ashely did not address the issue. In April I received another bill from the finance company with late fees. I gave the finance company a call and explained what Ashley had told me. The finance company stated they only bill based on the information Ashley reports to them. I made a trip to the Ashley store in Southaven where we made the purchase and asked to speak with a manager, which I got the run around. The manager that was suppose to assist me yelled at another assistant-manager, Cathy Bailey, to give me a hand. I presented all the paper work Ashely had provided me after the sale. The assistant manager looked over the paper work and asked if I had received a specific item on the couch billing. Which I say yes, because it was part of the bed order. She handed me the paper work and stated, “Well, that was why I was getting billed”. I explained that I was told I would NOT be billed until I received ALL the merchandise on the order. She admitted and stated the sales persons that sold us the merchandised lied to us and that there was NOTHING they could do. I guess I should have purchased a jar of Vaseline as well, because not only was I lied to I have now incurred late fees and they have dinged my credit, but at least the sales persons got their commission check.

I purchased furniture in August and was okay with the delay in delivery due to the pandemic but after having to return to the store because my incompetent sales associate didn’t completely my paperwork and receiving a text message in September that our furniture was ready for delivery and then calling the 800 number to find out that only 2/3 pieces were in stock and we would have to wait until the middle of October for the third piece, it was a little disappointing. I did not receive a phone call or text message in October so I called the 800 number again to find out that our third piece would not be in stock until November 7. I asked for partial delivery of the two pieces and was told the 800 number could not accommodate me with my request. I waited until after Nov 7 and called my local store and was told a partial delivery could be set up after November 11. I had to call the store again and was told my furniture was on layaway status due to the selling rep, CarolAnne not completing my paperwork so I had to look on my credit report to see who financed my account because it was never purchased on layaway. I was then told my paperwork would be updated and delivery scheduled. I called the next day after not receiving a return call and was told that my order was canceled. When I spoke with the manager she advised me there was nothing they could do except pick out new furniture and work with another sales associate. The answer was no! After years of being a customer to Ashley, they have lost my business and every referral I would send their way. Ridiculous!

Don’t purchase furniture here! You will regret it! Purchased furniture for den, dining room and living room in February. Waited 4 months for furniture to be delivered. At delivery one loveseat was broken and had to be reordered. After delivery men left I was looking at the kitchen bar. Opened the drawer and the wood was split on the drawer. . A few weeks later the broken loveseat finally got delivered only to find out it didn’t sit straight. It was whop side. One week later one of the other loveseats right side recliner broke. I had the wait three weeks for a technician to come out to tell me that the two loveseat and kitchen bar needed to be replaced. They didn’t just reorder a replacement for me. I had to keep calling and finally got a helpful lady who reordered my broken furniture for me. She didn’t understand what the problem was since this was new furniture that were already broken and neither did I. I’ve been waiting for the replacement furniture since June! You heard me correctly since June! They set up a delivery date today September 9, 2021 between 4:30-7:30pm, they were a no show! Yep! Still waiting! I would not recommend buying furniture here! Customer service is awful! I so wish I would have purchased my furniture somewhere else!!!!

May 22 I went to Ashley Homestore and ordered a house full of furniture. Everything was in stock at the time There was 2 different delivery dates on June 26 i recvd half my order. On July 1st I recvd some more. Except my bedroom set I only recvd the Chest So next schedule date was July 8 on that day it was delayed to July 17 on that day delayed to Aug 5 then Aug 19 then on that day Aug 27. Then Sept 5 now it says Sept 12 Just called to confirm today now they Say Sept 24.Cust care says the manufacturer changes the dates How is it possible for a manufacturer to fail to give a delivery date that many times. When you have a date means the items have shipped! They cannot provide me with a tracking ##..I am hearing that Ashley completes the orders from the 3rd party stores b4 delivering to customers. I just moved into my dream home on June 20 but me and my husband are sleeping on the floor. We didn't bring any old furniture from our old home We were excited to let Ashley furnish our entire home.. They say no manager is available. I have reached out to an Ashley Advocate hopefully I will get my issues resolved soon!!

Ashley Furniture HomeStore has horrible customer service...However my salesperson John Munn was great and helped pick out a dining room set that I loved! I purchased the set on June 29th at The Southaven, Ms location and it was delivered on July 7th however when it was delivered the hardware to put the table together was not with it. The delivery team told me that they will come back the next day with the hardware so that they could set the table up however no one came and I was not contacted by anyone. I contacted Ashley and they said that the delivery team had not notified them that the hardware was missing. After 3 weeks of going back and forth with no returned calls or sending someone to come out and put the table together so after the third week I notified Ashley that they could come to pick up the set. Once I did that I was left a voice message saying that the hardware was out for delivery. So here I am almost 4 weeks later with a table that has YET to be put together!! I'm very disappointed and would not recommend Ashley Furniture to anyone.

Let me start off saying that i love Ashley's Furniture however, yesterday's experience was the absolute worst. We visited the store May 21, 2020 looking to purchase a living room set. I was assigned a salesman named Jared. We looked around and came across a set that was discounted to $1500. I told my fiance lets get it and pay cash rather than getting it financed. Jared explained that it was discounted because that set would have to be purchased off the floor. We agreed. We were getting ready to ourchase it until i lwalked around the furniture and noticed a whole in the back of the love seat(he never mentioned the hole at this point) I told him that i wasnt paying that king of money for a set with a hole in it but if he knocked off a few hundred, we'd take it. His attitude was horrible. He said "i cant do that because its already discounted because of the whole thats in it". ( if i hadn't of noticed the hole, he would of never said a word) "The manager came and marked it down. I asked him to speak with her and he said she wouldnt be back in til next week. He just kept saying no. We decided to look at something else and he goes. I asked if he could call someone about the set. Then he says. "Theyre not going to give it away" my fiance told him, "we're paying our hard earned money no matter how much it is and that aint giving it away. Then he acts as if he agrees to sell it knocking off a few hundres so we sit down to complete the transaction and when he ask for payment, he onoy discounted it $100. I said no thank you and we left. This guy is definitely not for the customers and Ashley's have lost someone that been shopping with them for years. I told my mom an other relatives about our experience and that is one furniture store we wont use again.

I wish I could give this less than one star. I am beyond frustrated with Ashley. I purchased in January and still do not have all the pieces I ordered. I have made numerous attempts to contact them, however, no one seems to care. I get Bot responses when I post on social media. I’ve been hung up on at least 4 times during “transfers”. Corporate could care less. It has been a horrible experience. Part of my order was a bed that I was told wouldn’t house your standard mattress. I was told I had to have the adjustable base. Fine. I have no learned that is not true. The bed, mattress, and base were delivered and set up WITHOUT any of the power cords, so it’s basically your standard mattress, just a thousand dollars more than standard price. I’ve called and called and called and emailed and posted since the day it was delivered and am told I need to track the parts down from the manufacturer. Absolutely not. However, if you call the manufacturer, they tell you the store is responsible. It’s a revolving door of nonsense. My couch was delivered with only 3/4 of the pieces. After almost a month, I finally received the last piece. End tables are missing the pieces to hold the shelving. After all the time I have wasted on the phone trying to resolve this, Ashley Southaven should be cutting me a paycheck. I am ready to take all these pieces of non functional junk right back up to the store.

Ashley Furniture Homestore literally has the WORST service I have EVER received. I would not recommend them to ANYONE. I ordered a sectional over a month ago. They brought me two pieces to my delivery. It was missing the middle piece that connects the two. I talked to them 3 times the day of delivery and they failed to tell me I wasn’t receiving the entire piece of furniture that I had already purchased. The guys dropping off the furniture told me that it would be a whole month before I received the last piece. I called and told them I do not want the couch until I have the whole thing. They told me I would get the piece soon. The next day I received the notification that I would have a delivery in a week. I waited. That day came and the truck pulls up to my house and they DONT have what I needed. They have a piece that I already have. I called again. They see what I’m missing. They have a picture of my living room plus the signed paper of what I’m missing. But THEY FAILED to relay the message to the warehouse. She says she’s going to fix it immediately. The NEXT day I received ANOTHER message that I had a delivery for ANOTHER week away. I called immediately because I refused to be burned again. I ask WHAT are they delivering??? Again, she tells me THE WRONG PIECE. I tell her that this is ridiculous and all I want is what I have paid for and I have talked to them MULTIPLE TIMES and I DONT understand why they aren’t communicating with each other. This lady puts me on hold and fixed the issue right there and gets me a confirmation for the RIGHT piece. It is supposed to be delivered today. I just called them to check on the status of my delivery. THEY DONT HAVE IT. It was apparently loaded on the WRONG truck. And if I hadn’t called to check, NO ONE would have told me!! This business is unprofessional and unorganized. I DO NOT RECOMMEND.

I work in an industry where reviews and customer surveys have a huge impact on my work place so typically even when I recieve a bad experience I would just move on. My wife and I purchased a table and chairs from this location. They attempted to deliver the wrong table twice over the course of a month span ( 2 weeks wait time each time). On the second attempt they found they ordered the table incorrectly. Folks at the call center told me they could not do anything and the folks at the store said the manager was not in and I would have to wait. Not satisfied I pressed the issue and now someone was willing to help try to resolve the issue. After 2 days of waiting I was told the next time they could deliver the table was week and half away. No consideration for the time they had wasted of ours waiting for the table to be delivered. Fast forward to today. Wife waited all day for the table to be delivered. Right table and chairs although 2 chairs when scratched up and the table has a substantial chip on on edge. No biggie halfway expected this. All would have been fine had they not scratched up out brand new hardwood floor. Very disappointing experience all around. Would have been all forgived if someone had just take the time to say sorry and care about the situation.

DO NOT USE ASHLEY HOMESTORE!!! I will never use Ashley HOMESTORE ever again!!This has been the worst experience I have ever had with a company. They are full of empty promises just to make a sale. You never know if, or when you may receive your purchases. On February 13th 2019 I purchased a Sofa and love seat for my new apt. This was not my first choice due to the one I wanted would not be available until April. I went with a sofa that was going to be delivered on Feb 20th with the love seat being delivered on March 11th. On Feb 20th after confirming the sofa was on the way I got a call an hour later stating the Sofa was delayed until March 5th. March 8th I get confirmation both the sofa, and love seat will be delivered on March 12th. March 11th I call and get confirmation both will be delivered on time. ONE HOUR LATER I get a call the sofa is now delayed until APRIL 2nd!!!! But the love seat will still be delivered on the 12th between 2:15pm and 5:15pm. I leave work early to wait for the love seat. 5pm comes around and nothing! I call to see what’s going on. They tell me the love seat was again delayed until March 17th. WHAT the HECK is going on over at their warehouse? DOES anyone even have a clue? It has been over a month, and I do not have a couch to sit on. I still do not know if I will ever get the couches because they apparently don’t know ether. They just throw a date on your order, and hope for the best. DO NOT USE ASHLEY HOMESTORE. I want to stand in front of their store, and warn everyone that comes by. I have never been so frustrated in my life.

I went in Ashley Homestore in Southaven MS looking for a dresser but didn’t find one I liked. Somehow got in a conversation with my salesperson about the fact that I have hot flashes. He showed me a “temperature controlling” mattress protector and kept telling me how wonderful it was etc. It was pricey at $250 but if it helped at all it would be worth it even though he already knew I was on a very tight budget because I was going parttime at work and going back to school. As I was signing the receipt I realized that it had a No Return Policy, which he conveniently never mentioned. I was already checking out and it had been such a long process and plus it was supposed to be such a good product, I went ahead went the transaction. I got home and excitedly put it on my bed! That was the worse night of sleep I have ever had!!! It didn’t control the temperature even slightly and on top of that it moved too much so it was like I had to wrestle with it all night. So the next day I sent a text to my salesperson (he gave me a card and put his cell number because I planned to come back and get the night stands later that matched my bedroom suite). I wasn’t looking for a refund when I text him. I really thought he was nice and just wanted him to know how the product really was so that he would use caution when recommending it so highly in the future. And an apology would have been nice also since I financed $250 mattress protector that is packed up in originally container that it’s never been used and still is. I never received any reply. Nothing. This made be mad. A few weeks later I text asking if they had any special zero interest financing options that I could use to purchase the night stands. I got an immediate response!!!!! Needless to say I was very upset that he never responded to my complaint but immediately responded to another possible sale. I called him out on it in a text and he finally apologized saying that he didn’t see my original t cat until he got the new one. That he had hundred of text from family, friends and work that he hadn’t looked at yet. Wow! First of all I don’t believe that and secondly if that’s true then he shouldn’t give out his cell number to customers. Regardless he seen it when he seen the new message and chose to respond to the new one and not the old one at all until I said something and I gave him time to do so. In fact I responded normally to his response about the financing options and waited giving him a chance to comment on the other one before I went off about it. He shouldn’t have a job there! Then I went on Ashley’s website and emailed a complaint about the service I received and didn’t get a response from them either. I have spent about $20,000 with this company over the past seven years;however I will not ever spend another penny in there again. All they care about is making a dollar and they don’t care about customer satisfication at all. Well they just lost a long time customer who would have been back soon to purchase $1200 night stands. Not now though. Will never walk through those doors again. Customers beware!!!! Go somewhere where they care about you! Btw my sales person was Jonathan at Southaven ms. I do not recommend him at all
